==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pancreas
<hw>Pan"cre*as</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/;
<grk>pa^s</grk>, <grk>pa^n</grk>, all + <grk>kre`as</grk> flesh, meat:
cf. F. <ets>pancr⟦eacute⟧as</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The
sweetbread, a gland connected with the intestine of nearly all
vertebrates. It is usually elongated and light-colored, and its
secretion, called the pancreatic juice, is discharged, often together
with the bile, into the upper part of the intestines, and is a powerful
aid in digestion. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <cref>Digestive
apparatus</cref>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pancreatic</ent>⟦br⟧
